{
  "texts": [
    "The approach uses a syntactic dependency parser to identify opinion words grammatically linked to product characteristics, which are then used in a model of a campaign to identify characteristics most appealing to backers.",
    "The model developed in Babayoff and Shehory (2022) includes semantic features, such as LIWC keywords, custom crowdfunding-related \"buzzword\" lists, as well as topic models.",
    "The study finds that a model trained on semantic features alone performs on par with a model containing only metadata features, but the best results are obtained by combining both types of features.",
    "The study examines features with a strong correlation with funding success; it includes only LIWC and custom keywords, but not topic models.",
    "To predict project success, Cheng et al. (2019) train a deep neural network model operating on multimodal input: it incorporates features created from text, images and metadata of the project descriptions."
  ]
}